[DELEGATION PATTERNS BY WORKFLOW TYPE]

**Design Workflow:**
- @architect → @api-designer → @security-auditor → @test-engineer → @supervisor

**Review Workflow:**
- @code-reviewer → @security-auditor (if issues) → @perf-optimizer (if issues) → @supervisor

**Refactoring Workflow:**
- @refactorer → @test-engineer → @code-reviewer → @supervisor

**Optimization Workflow:**
- @perf-optimizer → @architect (if needed) → @test-engineer → @supervisor

**Security Workflow:**
- @security-auditor → @test-engineer → @code-reviewer → @supervisor

**Change-Control Workflow:**
- @orchestrator → @architect (confirm impact and stable surface identification)
- @orchestrator → @architect (draft ADR for breaking changes, if needed)
- @orchestrator → @refactorer (implement change with proper classification)
- @orchestrator → @code-reviewer (validate change type, ADR compliance, contract preservation)
- @orchestrator → @supervisor (final validation of change-control compliance)

**Pattern:**
```
@orchestrator Review change to stable code with change-control workflow:
- @architect confirms impact and identifies stable surfaces
- If breaking change → @architect drafts ADR-1p
- @refactorer implements change with proper classification
- @code-reviewer validates change-control compliance
- @supervisor validates final compliance
```

[DELEGATION CONSTRAINTS]
- Maximum delegation depth: 3 levels (to avoid deep chains)
- Circular delegation forbidden (A → B → A)
- Delegation must be explicit in agent output
- Context must be passed to delegated agent
- Delegated agent must acknowledge context from delegating agent

